I want to ask is it possible to have Unicode Text for windows titles? Unicode for Arabic, Persian language doesn't seems to work!

I used a string of font command with coding iso10646 and a font named "Yas" which have to support Persian completely. But it is not bidirectional!
 </description><pubDate>Wed, 04 Jul 2012 14:21:15 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/208/unicode-title-for-windows/</guid></item><item><title>Answer by Michael for &lt;p&gt;Hi.
I want to ask is it possible to have Unicode Text for windows titles? Unicode for Arabic, Persian language doesn't seems to work!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I used a string of font command with coding iso10646 and a font named "Yas" which have to support Persian completely. But it is not bidirectional!&lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/208/unicode-title-for-windows/?answer=209#post-id-209</link><description>Currently we only support X Core Fonts in the ISO10646 encoding. As you have noticed, different fonts include a varying amount of glyphs which may or may not be enough for your needs. Also, bidirectional titles are not supported at all with that solution.

There is an effort to support Xft fonts, though (see http://faq.i3wm.org/question/183/how-to-get-i3wm-font-anti-aliasing/</description><pubDate>Wed, 04 Jul 2012 14:27:47 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/208/unicode-title-for-windows/?answer=209#post-id-209</guid></item><item><title>Comment by joepd for &lt;p&gt;Currently we only support X Core Fonts in the ISO10646 encoding. As you have noticed, different fonts include a varying amount of glyphs which may or may not be enough for your needs. Also, bidirectional titles are not supported at all with that solution.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is an effort to support Xft fonts, though (see &lt;a href="http://faq.i3wm.org/question/183/how-to-get-i3wm-font-anti-aliasing/"&gt;http://faq.i3wm.org/question/183/how-...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/208/unicode-title-for-windows/?comment=216#comment-216</link><description>You can find it in [this tarball](https://aur.archlinux.org/packages/i3/i3-pango/i3-pango.tar.gz).  Found from [AUR](https://aur.archlinux.org/packages.php?ID=59344). </description><pubDate>Wed, 04 Jul 2012 20:45:54 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/208/unicode-title-for-windows/?comment=216#comment-216</guid></item><item><title>Comment by Shahin for &lt;p&gt;Currently we only support X Core Fonts in the ISO10646 encoding. As you have noticed, different fonts include a varying amount of glyphs which may or may not be enough for your needs. Also, bidirectional titles are not supported at all with that solution.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is an effort to support Xft fonts, though (see &lt;a href="http://faq.i3wm.org/question/183/how-to-get-i3wm-font-anti-aliasing/"&gt;http://faq.i3wm.org/question/183/how-...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
